## 5. Key Distinctions UGC NET Tests as Tricky MCQs

| Term | Meaning | Common confusion |
|---|---|---|
| Environmental Science | Interdisciplinary science studying environment | Confused with ecology |
| Ecology | Study of interactions between organisms and environment | A subset, not the whole |
| Environmental Studies | Broader than env. science; includes social science & humanities | Often used interchangeably but scope is wider |
| Environmentalism | A social movement, not a scientific discipline | Not the same as env. science |
| Sustainable Development | Brundtland 1987 definition | Source frequently asked |
| Precautionary Principle | Act before full scientific proof in case of serious risk | Appears in conventions like Rio Declaration (Principle 15) |
| Polluter Pays Principle | Financial liability on the polluter | Basis of Indian environmental laws |

---

## 6. Important Dates and Sources to Memorize

- **Brundtland Commission Report "Our Common Future"** — 1987 — gave the definition of Sustainable Development
- **Stockholm Conference** — 1972 — first major international recognition of environmental science as a policy field
- **Rio Earth Summit** — 1992 — Agenda 21, CBD, UNFCCC
- The term "Environmental Science" as a distinct academic field emerged in the **1960s–70s** with Rachel Carson's *Silent Spring* (1962) acting as a catalyst
